Abstract
We do archaeology on Earth concerning the origins of humans and their thoughts about the
world around them from ancient to modern times. The moon orbits the earth once in about 30
days, and does twelve of these revolutions in the time it takes the Earth to go around the Sun.
The Druids who built Stonehenge knew this, and the Mayans who built their pyramids in
Mexico observed it, and well as the Egyptians who built the Great Pyramid of Giza. All of these
structures have celestial alignments, and the calendar we have today came from such
knowledge of these ancients. But can we surmise what kind of calendar came into existence
from the ancient astronomers of a planet orbiting another star? The stars are out of our reach,
at least for resolving a moon orbiting a planet orbiting a star, but we can ascertain that planets
exist around other stars, and even infer their mass, and orbital period. If we can start to know
these things about other star systems, is it possible other life has begun to know them about
ours. Or, have they perhaps even been here, or are they here now? I look into this here.!

The Alpha Centauri Star System
Alpha Centauri is the nearest of the stars to us and is a triple system designated Alpha
Cenatauri A, B, And C. Alpha Cenauri A and B are much like the sun, similar in mass and
luminosity. Alpha Centauri A is is 1.1 solar masses and Alpha Centauri B is 0.907 solar masses.
They orbit a common center, which can be taken as the focus of an ellipse at the center of
gravity between the two. The period is 79.91 years, which means the its semi-major axis is
given by its orbital period using Kepler’s law of planetary motion, which is if we work with units
of earth years and astronomical units (AU):"
"

The distance to the Alpha Centauri system is perfect for a ﬁrst interstellar mission because it is
only 4.24 light years away if we measure the distance to it to be from the Sun to Alpha Centauri
C (Also called Proxima Centauri) the closest of the three stars and a much less massive, much
less luminous than the Sun red dwarf with an earth sized planet in its habitable zone
discovered in 2016 and a super-earth sized planet at 1.5 AU from it, which is the distance Mars
is from the Sun, roughly (1.52 AU)."
Alpha Centauri A is thought to have a Neptune sized planet in its habitable zone. While A and B
orbit one another their closest approach is 11.2 AU, and furtherest is 35.6 AU, but C (Proxima
Centauri) has its orbit very far from these two at 0.21 light years, a whopping 13,000 AU! The
11.2 and 35.6 AU for A and B are distances like Saturn and Pluto from the Sun, respectively.
Let us compute the vitals for this star system. To do that I will ﬁrst explain how the annual
average temperature is determined for a planet, and then write a program that does this for us,
and use it. It will include how we determine the habitable zone of a star system, and it will
calculate it as well."

The Program
The program in C is as follows:"
#include <stdio.h>
#include<math.h>
int main(int argc, const char * argv[]) {
{
float s, a, l, b, r, AU, N, root, number, answer, C, F;
printf("We determine the surface temperature of a planet.\n");
printf("What is the luminosity of the star in solar luminosities?
");
scanf("%f", &s);
printf("What is the albedo of the planet (0-1)?" );
scanf("%f", &a);
printf("What is the distance from the star in AU? ");
scanf("%f", &AU);
r=1.5E11*AU;
l=3.9E26*s;
b=l/(4*3.141*r*r);
N=(1-a)*b/(4*(5.67E-8));
root=sqrt(N);
number=sqrt(root);
answer=1.189*(number);
printf("\n");
printf("\n");
printf("The surface temperature of the planet is: %f K\n",
answer);

Running The Program
Here we use a single atmospheric layer with no
convection for the planet to be in an equilibrium
state. That is to say, the temperature stays
steady by heat gain and loss with radiative
heat transfer alone.
The habitable zone is calculated using the idea
that the earth is in the habitable zone for a
star like the Sun. That is, if a star is 100
times brighter than the Sun, then the habitable
zone for that star is ten times further from
it than the Earth is from the Sun because ten
squared is 100.
